"{\"uid\": \"si.com-college-texas-news-former-texas-basketball-star-kevin-durant-brings-home-olympic-gold-medal-from-paris-01j4z2x69yjr\", \"text\": \"In this story:  Kevin Durant,the formerTexas Longhornsgreat, won his fourth Gold Medal Saturday afternoon in Paris. He teamed up with 10 other NBA All-Stars to turn back the home-standing French team, 98-87. It might have been the most difficult road game for Team USA ever.  Durant, who this week became theall-time leading scorer in U.S. Olympic Basketball history,now holds the record for the most Gold Medals won. He finished the final game with 15 points.  The big man left Texas in 2007 to enter the NBA Draft, where he was the second pick of the first round by the Seattle Supersonics. His jersey was retired by Texas in a special ceremony in 2009.  France'sVictor Wembanyama, who plays for the San Antonio Spurs, scored 26 points and grabbed seven rebounds in the loss. Wembanyama will bring a silver medal back to the Lone Star state.  Durant made news the morning of the game as he was being taunted and trolled by Denver Nuggets fans for comments he made about Nikola Jokic after the semifinal game against Serbia. A reporter forThe Denver Postreferred to Durant as a putz.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cTo all you nuggets fans, nobody gives a (expletive) who yall lames believe is the best player in the league,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d KD tweeted, adding, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cplayers got major respect for Jok, we don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t worship him like yall do but most are in awe of his brilliance. Trolling you cornballs for rooting against us is apart of the game. Deal (with) it.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Sean Keeler, the columnist for The Denver Post, wrote that many fans in Denver were rooting against Team USA due to Durant's comments about Jokic.  Regardless of all the trash talk, Durant has now added another Gold Medal to his resume.  Loading recommendations... Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations    \\u00c